    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix potential undefined behavior in PRACH slot calculation due to uninitialized num_slots\n\n### Summary\nThe `find_nr_prach` function could exhibit undefined behavior when searching through PRACH entries. The `num_slots` field in `prach_item_t` structures was not being initialized during list initialization, potentially containing garbage values. When the search condition `(p->slot + p->num_slots - 1) == slot` was evaluated, this could lead to unpredictable results.\n\nThis fix ensures all `prach_item_t` fields are properly initialized to prevent undefined behavior.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/NR_TRANSPORT/nr_prach.c`: Initialize `num_slots` field to 0 in both `init_prach_list()` and `free_nr_prach_entry()` functions to ensure consistent and predictable behavior during PRACH slot calculations.\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder certain conditions with specific frame/slot values, the PRACH detection could fail to match valid entries or incorrectly match invalid ones due to garbage values in uninitialized `num_slots` field. This could manifest as missed RACH detections or false positives in PRACH processing.\n"
}